Fix window leak upon exiting MainActivity

AlertDialogs are tied to the current window, in this case MainActivity.
Once MainActivity is closed upon calling finish(), the AlertDialog is
not dismissed yet and thus causes a memory leak.

Fix this by dismissing the AlertDialog before closing MainActivity.

Signed-off-by: Zhao Wei Liew <zhaoweiliew@gmail.com>

Add support for override_vmin

Adds support for a simple 0/1 attribute at
/sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/override_vmin.  When enabled on
kernels that support it, this attribute forces CPU voltage to remain
above a safe limit.

This commit also bolts a setFullSpan method onto SwitchCompatCardItem to
allow the override_vmin card to display correctly in the CPU Voltage
fragment.

Signed-off-by: Ryan Pennucci <decimalman@gmail.com>

Introducing Kernel downloader
An option to download third party kernels from developers. This works with JSON files. Kernel developers have to maintain their JSON database and keep them up to date. I will write up a documentation, so people can easily add support for their kernel.

Recovery: Add option for Soft Reboot

Option for soft reboot/hot reboot by killing zygote. All the services and apps registered to zygote gets killed and restarted. This effectively decreases reboot time when someone just wants to restart all the apps. The effect is mostly noticeable on older devices.

Busybox is required for pkill/killall commands.

MSM_Hotplug: Use debug string over debug mask string
